5.4.20  8:08 pm   Do you ever reach the point where you've sunk so much time and energy into a bigger project and you haven't bitten off more than you can chew but it would be easier to drop the thing and go back to doing whatever you made before?

     yes but no

     It's an issue I've been faced with and I wonder if it's my failing mental state or an common creative problem

5.4.20  7:53 pm   Have you ever submitted a question to yourself through this page?

      absolutely not

      animation nodes

      pretty good

5.4.20  7:50 pm   Do you find working on more operational and process related concerns, such as re-inventing the graphics department and streamlining processes for shorter turnaround times, as enjoyable as working on music and videos?

      yes and no

5.4.20  7:49 pm   How do you get the crazy text effects in your editing software? I've been trying and I can't make it look quite as good as in your videos.

      try this: try doing whatever simple operations you might do, and then export it as a video and re-import it again. then operate on that. this might be the key to getting that additional level of subtlety you crave, and may bring you one step closer into the 'how did they do that' realm

     Was it inspiration?

     that is what fuels songwriting in general

     Was it a future prediction?

     songs in general have a tendency to be laced with future prediction

      What about the land of the 2 letter words? What gave you that idea?

     the previous line, assumedly

     I have so many more questions I can't fit in this!
